《'''復興：埃爾圖魯爾'''》（{{Lang-tr|Diriliş: Ertuğrul}}，{{lang-en|Resurrection: Ertuğrul}}）是一套[[土耳其|土耳其]][[電視影集|電視影集]]，是历史古裝剧類型。這齣電視劇的时代背景是13世纪的土耳其，主角是[[鄂图曼帝国|鄂图曼帝国]]創立人[[奥斯曼一世|奥斯曼一世]]的父亲[[埃尔图鲁尔加齐|埃尔图鲁尔加齐]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/resurrection-ertugrul-currently-on-netflix-far-exceeds-its-reputation-as-a-turkish-game-of-thrones-8576051.html |title=Resurrection: Ertuğrul, currently on Netflix, far exceeds its reputation as a ‘Turkish Game of Thrones' |publisher=First Post |accessdate=2020-07-09 |archive-date=2022-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203113133/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/resurrection-ertugrul-currently-on-netflix-far-exceeds-its-reputation-as-a-turkish-game-of-thrones-8576051.html }}</ref>

此劇在不少穆斯林国家包括[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]和[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]热播，但在[[埃及|埃及]]等阿拉伯国家却被禁播。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dw.com/en/ertugrul-muslim-game-of-thrones-grips-pakistani-viewers/a-54026833 |title=Ertugrul: 'Muslim Game of Thrones' grips Pakistani viewers |website=DW |date=2020-07-02 |accessdate=2020-08-21 |archive-date=2022-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220220081542/https://www.dw.com/en/ertugrul-muslim-game-of-thrones-grips-pakistani-viewers/a-54026833 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.trtworld.com/magazine/what-s-behind-the-ertugrul-craze-in-pakistan-36214 |title=What’s behind the Ertugrul craze in Pakistan? |publisher=TRT World |accessdate=2020-05-11 |archive-date=2021-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411235118/https://www.trtworld.com/magazine/what-s-behind-the-ertugrul-craze-in-pakistan-36214 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-53024479 |title=Ertugrul: The Turkish TV drama enthralling Pakistan |publisher=BBC |accessdate=2020-06-15 |archive-date=2022-01-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220130183555/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-53024479 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.albawaba.com/editors-choice/egyptian-fatwa-calls-muslims-boycott-ertugrul-other-turkish-soaps-1338629 |title=Egyptian Fatwa Calls on Muslims to Boycott Ertugrul, Other Turkish Soaps |publisher=Al Bawada |accessdate=2020-02-12}}</ref>

